#: ../../G/gubbish.rst:9
msgid ""
"[a portmanteau of ‘garbage’ and ‘rubbish’; may have originated with SF "
"author Philip K. Dick] Garbage; crap; nonsense. \"What is all this "
"gubbish?\" The opposite portmanteau ‘rubbage’ is also reported; in fact, it "
"was British slang during the 19th century and appears in Dickens."
msgstr ""
"[‘garbage’と‘rubbish’のかばん語。SF作家Philip K. Dickに由来するかもしれない] "
"ゴミ、くだらないもの、ナンセンス。「このgubbishは全部何だ?」逆のかばん語‘rubbage’も報告されている。実際、それは19世紀のイギリスのスラングで、Dickensにも現れる。"
